===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|smoothe|lang=enm}}, {{term|smothe|lang=enm}}, {{term|smethe|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|smoþ|smōþ|lang=ang}}, {{term|smoþe|smōþe|smooth, serene, calm, unruffled|lang=ang}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|smeþe|smēþe|smooth, polished, soft, without roughness or inequalities of surface, without discomfort or annoyance, suave, agreeable, avoiding offence, not irritating, not harsh, melodious, harmonious, lenitive|lang=ang}}, both from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|smanþaz|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|smanþiz||smooth, soft|lang=gem-pro}}, of unknown origin. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|smuith||smooth|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|smode|lang=nds}}, {{term|smoede|lang=nds}}, {{term|smoe||smooth|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|smödig||smooth, malleable, ductile|lang=nds}}.

